---
import type { CollectionEntry } from 'astro:content';
export interface Props { font: CollectionEntry<'fonts'>['data']; }
const { font } = Astro.props;
const fam = font.fontFamily;
---
<div class="iu" style={`--fam:${fam}`}>
  <!-- 01 — realistic long-form reading (a body face's true home) -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">01</span><span class="label">Long read — set at real reading size (18px)</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene">
      <div class="read">
        <div class="read__head">
          <span class="read__kicker">The Quarterly · Essay</span>
          <h3 class="read__title">In Praise of the Unnoticed Letter</h3>
          <span class="read__byline">by A. Compositor · 8 min read</span>
        </div>
        <div class="read__body">
          <p><span class="read__drop">T</span>here is a particular kind of craft that succeeds only by disappearing. A body typeface does its best work when you finish a paragraph without once having thought about the shapes that carried it. Libre Baskerville was drawn for exactly that: not to be admired, but to be read, at length, on a screen, without fatigue.</p>
          <p>Its designers took a two-hundred-year-old face built for ink and paper and asked a simpler, harder question — what would it take to read this comfortably at sixteen pixels in a browser tab? The answer was a list of quiet compromises: a taller x-height, wider counters, a gentler contrast, each trading a little elegance for a great deal of stamina.</p>
          <blockquote class="read__quote">“The best body type is a window, not a painting. You are meant to look through it.”</blockquote>
          <p>Set a long passage and the proof arrives on its own. The eye settles into a rhythm; the page holds an even colour; the serifs lay down a firm baseline that gently pulls you from one word to the next. This is typography as hospitality — the art of making a reader feel, for a few thousand words, completely at home.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">A text face shown the way it actually lives — in a column you read.</p>
  </figure>

  <!-- 02 — editorial pull quote -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">02</span><span class="label">Editorial — the pull quote</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene scene21">
      <div class="iu__poster pq">
        <span class="pq__mark">“</span>
        <p class="pq__text">A good letter outlives its purpose; it was cut for candlelight and reads just as kindly by the glow of a screen.</p>
        <span class="pq__attr">— on the long life of Baskerville</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </figure>
</div>

<style>
  .iu__item { margin: 0; }
  .iu__hint { margin-top: var(--sp-2); color: var(--fg-3); }
  .scene21 { aspect-ratio: 21 / 9; }

  /* Realistic reading column — real px, not container-scaled */
  .read { font-family: var(--fam); background: var(--bg); padding: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3.5rem); }
  .read__head { max-width: 62ch; margin: 0 auto var(--sp-5); text-align: center; }
  .read__kicker { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent); }
  .read__title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); line-height: 1.1; font-weight: 700; margin: 0.6rem 0; }
  .read__byline { font-style: italic; color: var(--fg-3); font-size: 15px; }
  .read__body { max-width: 64ch; margin: 0 auto; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--fg); }
  .read__body p + p { margin-top: 1.2em; }
  .read__drop { float: left; font-size: 3.4em; line-height: 0.72; padding: 0.05em 0.12em 0 0; font-weight: 700; color: var(--accent); }
  .read__quote { font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.4; font-style: italic; margin: 1.4em 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; border-left: 2px solid var(--accent); color: var(--fg); }

  .pq { background: var(--bg); display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; padding: 4cqi 6cqi; }
  .pq__mark { font-size: 16cqi; line-height: 0.6; color: var(--accent); }
  .pq__text { font-size: 5cqi; line-height: 1.25; font-style: italic; color: var(--fg); max-width: 80%; margin-top: -2cqi; }
  .pq__attr { font-size: 2.6cqi; color: var(--fg-3); margin-top: 2cqi; }

  @container (max-width: 600px) {
    .read__body { font-size: 16px; }
  }
</style>
